?TOP STORIES

PPL CORPORATION TO DEVELOP $305M POWER PLANT NEAR CHICAGO

PPL Corp. plans to develop a $305 million power plant near Chicago and will 
boost the capacity of a second plant in response to increasing demand for 
electricity.

WASHINGTON STATE SENATE PASSES ENERGY BILL IN COMPROMISE

The Senate passed a compromise energy bill Thursday, rolling together several 
proposals aimed at promoting conservation and new power generation.

GE POWER SYSTEMS TO SUPPLY TURBINES, SERVICES FOR NEWPORT GENERATION'S NEW 
1300-MW FACILITY IN WASHINGTON STATE - NEW PLANT WILL HELP MEET PACIFIC 
NORTHWEST'S GROWING NEED FOR POWER

Newport Generation, Inc. of Irvine, CA and GE Power Systems of Atlanta, GA 
announced today that GE has received contracts totaling $375 million to 
supply four gas turbines, two steam turbines and contractual services for a 
new 1,300-megawatt combined-cycle power plant in the state of Washington. 

CONSTELLATION ENERGY GROUP GROWS 8 NEW PLANTS FOR NATIONAL MARKET

Constellation Energy Group, one of the nation's fastest growing merchant 
energy companies, is scheduled to bring four "peaking" power plants on line 
this summer with four larger power plants scheduled to enter service in the 
summers of 2002 and 2003.

FERC WEIGHS PRICE RELIEF IN CALIFORNIA STAGE 3 EMERGENCIES

U.S. Federal Energy Regulatory Commission member William Massey said on 
Monday the central part of a staff recommendation for giving price relief to 
California wholesale power markets is a plan to limit prices during severe 
electricity shortages in the state.

U.S. PSEG TO BUILD $335 MLN POWER PLANT IN POLAND

U.S. Public Service Enterprise Group on Monday began building a $335 million 
power and heating plant in Poland as part of its expansion plans in the 
eastern European country. 


